This async Python code has a subtle race condition that causes duplicate payments ~0.1% of the time. Find it and fix it:

```python
class PaymentService:
    def __init__(self, db, stripe_client):
        self.db = db
        self.stripe_client = stripe_client
        self._processing = set()

    async def process_payment(self, order_id: str, amount: float):
        if order_id in self._processing:
            return {'status': 'already_processing'}

        self._processing.add(order_id)

        try:
            existing = await self.db.get_payment(order_id)
            if existing and existing.status == 'completed':
                return {'status': 'already_paid'}

            charge = await self.stripe_client.charge(amount)
            await self.db.save_payment(order_id, charge.id, 'completed')
            return {'status': 'success', 'charge_id': charge.id}
        finally:
            self._processing.discard(order_id)
```

Explain the race window, demonstrate how it leads to double charges, and provide a fix using database-level locking.

